						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Dwedit wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">You can use the same solution again, and have a linked list of empty slots, so there will be no need to scan. When you need a free slot, just grab the first one and make the second one the new first, and when you free a slot you can do the opposite. Memory use will just increase by 1 byte, the one used to indicate the first free slot, because objects can't be in both lists, so you can still get away with only one byte per object indicating the next one.<br /></div><br /><br />Wow, never thought of this trick.  That's a great idea!</div>
